<p><b>What is xmon?</b>
<p><img SRC="data/xfmon.jpg" NOSAVE height=134 width=310>
<br><font size=-1>1) screenshot of xmon</font>
<p>Xmon is an extended cluster monitoring package, written from scratch
by Marc O. Gloor. There is a precompiled binary of Xmon available now -
note that this i386-binary is just an early snapshot from current development
state. Published under the General Public License. Use it at your own risk.
Please report bugs to the author. Sources are not available yet - be patient.
d18 13
a30 2
<p><b>Cluster interconnection figure (planned)</b>
<p><img SRC="data/xmon_chart.jpg" NOSAVE height=378 width=391>
d32 2
d35 10
a44 64
<p><b>History</b>
<ul>
<li>
strange memory lag&nbsp; <font color="#FF0000">[in progress]</font></li>

<li>
bad display refresh rate (xlib implementation for a faster display refresh
rate was a lot of work)&nbsp; <font color="#FF0000">[fixed in 0.0.2]</font></li>

<li>
<font color="#000000">host name output in title bar</font><font color="#FF0000">
[done in 0.0.3]</font></li>

<li>
text size to large&nbsp; <font color="#FF0000">[fixed in 0.0.2]</font></li>

<li>
background grid color allocation failed (colormap fix in progress) <font color="#FF0000">[fixed
in 0.0.2]</font></li>

<li>
xmond - socket daemon for parallel computing networks&nbsp; <font color="#FF0000">[under
construction]</font></li>

<li>
xmon socket connection to xmond&nbsp; <font color="#FF0000">[planned]</font></li>

<li>
resizing doesn't work&nbsp; <font color="#FF0000">[planned]</font></li>

<li>
counter overflow after 65'000 loops (about 20h runtime)&nbsp; <font color="#FF0000">[under
construction]</font></li>

<li>
no CLI options available&nbsp; <font color="#FF0000">[under construction]</font></li>

<li>
<font color="#000000">key press event support</font><font color="#FF0000">
[planned]</font></li>

<li>
no interrupt output&nbsp; <font color="#FF0000">[not supported]</font></li>

<li>
<font color="#000000">create tarball package distribution (Makefiles...)
</font><font color="#FF0000">[under
construction]</font></li>

<li>
Other Unices currently not supported (AIX, Solaris, Irix, HP-UX...) <font color="#FF0000">[libgtop
implementation planned]</font></li>

<li>
<font color="#000000">and all what you suggest!</font></li>
</ul>

<p><br><b>Download XFmon alpha unstable versions for testing purposes</b>
<ul>
<li>
13.6.2000 [4.2Kb]: <a href="data/xmon_0.0.3-alpha.i386.bin.gz">xmon_0.0.3-alpha.i386.bin.gz</a><tt>
(MD5:1fe020e23ec767691b65b846afe7e874)</tt></li>
</ul>

